Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ContainerInterface
    Container Interface represents the interface for the Container Class The class that uses this interface uses a Stack of DonationPackage to simulate stacking and removing DonationPackages to and from the container.
    DonationManageInterface
    DonationManagerInterface class simulates the operation of adding a new package to the container stack, adding a new volunteer to the volunteer line, adding a new recipient to the recipient line and donating a package from the container by the volunteer to the recipient.
    QueueInterface<T>
    Interface for a Queue data structure
    RecipientLineInterface  
    StackInterface<T>
    Interface for a generic Stack data structure
    VolunteerLineInterface
    VolunteerLine Interface represents the interface for the VolunteerLine Class The class that uses this interface uses a Queue of Volunteers to simulate queuing and dequeuing volunteers to and from the VolunteerLine.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Container
    Container This class uses a Stack of DonationPackage to simulate stacking and removing DonationPackages to and from the container.
    DonationManager
    The DonationManager class will manage adding a new package to the container, a new volunteer to the volunteer queue line , a new recipient to the recipient queue and donating package by the volunteer to the recipient.
    DonationManagerTest  
    DonationPackage
    DonationPackage Holds the information of the package to be donated: description, weight.
    GuiDriver
    GuiDriver class is the Gui driver This is where the Gui stage is set up and creates a new Gui Main
    GuiMain
    GuiMain Prompts user to enter a password and re-type the password It is where the password, file, exit buttons, textfields and labels are created, exceptions are thrown, and PasswordChecker class is called
    MyQueue<T>
    MyQueue Generic queue class called MyQueue to implement the queue of volunteers and recipients line.
    MyStack<T>
    MyStack Generic stack class called MyStack to place the DonationPackage on a Container.
    Recipient
    Recipient Holds the information of the recipients: name
    RecipientLine
    RecipientLine RecipientLine class will implement the RecipientLineInterface class.
    Volunteer
    Volunteer Holds the relevant information for a Volunteer: name.
    VolunteerLine
    VolunteerLine VolunteerLine class will implement the VolunteerLineInterface.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ContainerException
    ContainerException If the user attempts to add new Donation Package and the Container line is full (5 packages).
    RecipientException
    RecipientException If the user attempts to add new Recipient and the recipient line is full (5 recipients).
    VolunteerException
    VolunteerException If the user attempts to add new Volunteer and the volunteer line is full (5 volunteers).
